Please monitor NOAA weather radio, radio and TV stations for emergency weather information. Thank you.

post_text:
We made it!!! Thank you to all the students, families, and staff for all of your hard work this past year (and especially these past few months)! To celebrate we have a virtually field day(s) and invite everyone to participate. The field day(s) will be held today (Tuesday) and tomorrow (Wednesday).

Students- make sure to keep track and email your score to Mrs. Culjan (bculjan@wesd185.org) by midnight on Wednesday. By doing so, you can be recognized on the school Facebook page for earning a virtual gold, silver, or bronze metal! Also, we would love to see pictures of you and your family completing the activities! You can email those to Mrs. Culjan as well.

The virtual field day is attached and you will find that each activity has an explanation and possible modifications. If you need to further modify the activity so that it will work in your environment that is completely fine.

Have Fun! You have earned it!



https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1bKpyBsnZ2omn0H3VE0wAiWa_WXzx6Pcq6Tr3glN8Jiw/edit?usp=sharing

post_text:
Featured 8th Grader: Bailey P.

Favorite memory from my time at Waltham-
One of my favorite memories from Waltham are the ones made at games and practices. I enjoyed basketball practices with Lexa and Lia, and I enjoyed jamming out to music at the volleyball practices. The parent nights were also an amazing event to experience with our coaches, Bruce, Shannon, Amy, and Reece. But, I have made many other memories with the teachers and staff at Waltham, that I will hold on to for a lifetime.

What I will miss the most-
I will miss the teachers willingness to help us achieve our goals by teaching us, but also their ability to make things fun and interesting at the same time. I will also miss the inside jokes we have with the teachers and how everyone knows each other by name.

What I am looking forward to in highschool-
The thing I am looking forward to most are the upcoming basketball and track seasons, meeting new people and teachers, and the experiences that come along with being in highschool.

Bailey- You will be missed. Good luck in all things you do, you will do amazing!

shared_text:
Waltham Elementary School #185
April 20 at 9:13 AM ¬∑

Feed His Children is having a "Drive-Thru Donation Day" on Saturday, April 25 from 10-2. The list of items we're asking for is in the photo below, as well as a traffic flow map of the Crossbridge Peru campus.

Grocery stores are just starting to allow us to order again, so the more that we get, the more we'll be able to bless the families we serve. We do ask that people purchase no more than three of each item to be respectful of everyone!

People donating will just drive up, open their trunks, and a volunteer will take the food out of their trunk, so there's no contact at all.

Thanks for considering donating to this cause that supports our area families.

I'm looking forward to starting a new journey in high school and seeing where it leads me.

Bridgit- We will miss you!

LaSalle County Historical Society Museum
March 19 at 4:25 PM ¬∑

***PLEASE SHARE***
We would like to announce a new ‚ÄúLocal History Project‚Äù from the LaSalle County Historical Society. With many students and families at home and many of our elderly residents experiencing complete isolation we have created a questionnaire to learn more about our county‚Äôs rich history from those who have lived it. Please consider taking the time to reach out to an elderly family member or friend. This is a wonderful way to teach our youth about our local history as well as bring back nostalgic memories to those whom may be experiencing loneliness during this difficult time. This questionnaire is available on our website at www.lasallecountyhistoricalsociety.org or by emailing office@lasallecountyhistoricalsociety.org

During this unprecedented time, thank you for your patience and understanding. The school office will be open from 9-1 daily (Monday-Friday) during the mandated closure. If you need to pick up a packet or other items, please call to set up a time if you are unable to during the above time.

Teachers will be available via email from 9-2 daily (Monday-Friday) to assist students with work as needed. The ISBE is not mandating e-learning, but the teachers and staff at Waltham are highly encouraging your child to complete the tasks they have provided. This will help your child to #keeplearning.

Please check our facebook page to look for ways to be digitally engaged with other families as a Waltham community.

Please check backpacks and lunchboxes, we had all students go through lockers and cubbies before leaving school today. This would be a great time to wash and sanitize backpacks and lunchboxes.



Thank you,

Waltham Staff

Waltham PTCC
March 7 at 4:41 PM ¬∑

Thank you to a handful of volunteers who helped make our Scholastic Book Fair a HUGE success last week!

Also a BIG thank you goes out to our Waltham Families for all their purchases to help us not only reach, but to blow our $2,500 goal out of the water!! Our total fair sales were $4,297!! That‚Äôs amazing!! That‚Äôs almost double the fall fair!

With the goal met, and surpassed we decided to purchase a book for every student! So each and every student will be coming home with a new book!

With our library & birthday books stocked pretty well, we will also be giving teachers a budget to spend at Scholastic for their classrooms!

Thank for your support!!
Waltham PTCC Book Fair Committee

post_text:
Why donate toys to Kindness Club‚Äôs toy drive?
Ms. Blue says, ‚ÄúWhen my son, at 9 months old, had to undergo testing at the Peoria Children‚Äôs Hospital, it was a hard day for our whole family. But, when we got there, the nurses immediately provided toys which kept him calm and happy through the ordeal. His favorite was a stuffed donkey, which they let him take home! At the time he would cuddle the donkey and say, ‚ÄòBabababababa,‚Äô so naturally we named the donkey Bob! Even now, almost a year later, Bob the Donkey is still a favorite toy! We had one hard day, but because of the kindness of others‚Äô toy donations, we made it through and even have happy memories to cherish. Please consider donating the the Kindness Club‚Äôs Toy Drive.‚Äù
